  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: cd8f8ce2fb929114f841c9e41beb59b6, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::ModuleContentController
  moduleImage: {fileID: 389737256}
  descriptionText: {fileID: 1386805885}
  moduleImages:
  - {fileID: -3509744016396952904, guid: 0d002fa15b2107a45ba222051c44e0f9, type: 3}
  - {fileID: -1428842927867859598, guid: 51641c21f0a91994c97aa00380e2368c, type: 3}
  - {fileID: -279384441923056290, guid: ad76f1582c1d3db4aaf6118cf42684aa, type: 3}
  - {fileID: 8060290372991731381, guid: 39210c3a2cd82cc45a82f1214540fe3e, type: 3}
  - {fileID: -1183258822137341215, guid: 35106df7141a8064ab869c647f2a74ba, type: 3}
  - {fileID: -3879085592048706892, guid: c49efe31438787542b6fe36862ad4ce2, type: 3}
  - {fileID: -831882446358543753, guid: 217ef956fd10a894196eb09c57ca4b93, type: 3}
  - {fileID: 591839109534253858, guid: 5d36ebb6c469a044ba54ffae0e73da60, type: 3}
  - {fileID: 4174409966628935797, guid: fe117d71edb7a35478550d8ac68b7109, type: 3}
  descriptions:
  - This area contains all the components and devices needed to complete your tasks.
  - This is the area where you perform tasks such as building a PC and setting up
    networks.
  - 'This area provides immediate feedback on your actions within the workspace.

    By
    dragging a component to the left side of the Terminal Area, you can view its
    description.'
  - 'This is where all assigned tasks are displayed. Tasks may vary depending on
    the lesson.

'
  - 'To complete a task, press and hold M1 (left mouse button)to drag a selected
    component or device. Release M1 to drop the item into the workspace.

'
  - "Select a component (e.g., CPU) and drag it to its corresponding slot (CPU slot).
    \r\nRepeat the same process for other components (BIOS chip, GPU, RAM, SSD) by
    placing them in their respective slots. \r\nOnce all components are correctly
    installed, drag and drop the completed motherboard into the PC case to assemble
    the system unit. \r\nConnect the system unit to the monitor by dragging the VGA
    cable and attaching it to both devices. \r\nPress the AVR buttonto complete the
    installation. The process will only succeed if all components and connections
    are correct. \r\nNote:\r\nIf a mistake is made, press the Eject Button on top
    of the PC case to remove the motherboard and return all components to their original
    positions."
  - "Opens the main menu where you can:\r\nSelect levels \r\nReview lessons in the
    Lesson Book \r\nAccess the User Manual \r\n"
  - "Allows you to customize the game based on your preferences, such as:\r\nSound
    and music volume \r\ndrag the slider left and right depending on how loud you
    want it to be.\r\nScreen resolution \r\nA pre-selected choices are provided what
    resolution are suitable for you.\r\n"
  - Closes the game.
